{/* ---------- SECTION 1 ---------- */}

Watch out for email scams

{/* Divider Line */}
{/* Description */}

Be cautious of emails asking for personal information. Scammers often pretend to be trusted companies. Always double-check before clicking links.

{/* View More */}
{/* ---------- SECTION 2 ---------- */}

Pay with a credit card

{/* Divider Line */}
{/* Description */}

Credit cards offer better fraud protection than debit cards or cash payments. Always choose secure payment methods.

{/* View More */}
{/* ---------- SECTION 3 ---------- */}

Check your statements

{/* Divider Line */}
{/* Description */}

Regularly review your bank and credit card statements to detect any unauthorized transactions early.

{/* View More */}
{/* ---------- SECTION 4 ---------- */}

Report the company

{/* Divider Line */}
{/* Description */}

If a company seems suspicious or has scammed you, report it immediately. This helps protect other users and sends warnings to authorities.

{/* View More */}
